Job Description
Aligns the team to work towards department goals and CoE goals.Contributes to product architecture and functionality decisions.Contributes to quality metric definition.Ensure lessons learned are propagated across team to increase institutional knowledge.Ensures development processes and RASSUI quality standards are adhered.Establishes functional procedure and policy.Facilitates cross team communication to resolve impediments.Identifies risks and defines mitigation plans.Interacts with internal or external customers to understand/ negotiate information on projects/ products and development activities.Keeps expenses within budget.Provides budget input for capital expenditure and operational expenses of the team.Provides feedback to managers on career path and guides them in continuous development and learning.Recognizes, addresses, escalates personnel related impediments of the team.Responsible for complete end to end project management including release planning, delivery, monitoring progress, and reporting.Responsible for conducting appraisals, feedback, and handling work allocations for direct reports and approving the same for indirect reports.Responsible for developing appropriate processes and road map including technology, hiring plans, training requirements, staffing.Responsible for identifying functional linkages across the organization for inter departmental collaboration.Responsible for overseeing the development, support, maintenance, and implementation of projects and product through managers.Reviews project milestones, deliverables, and quality.Reviews quality metrics and determines remediation plans.Uses expert people management skills to attract, motivate, and retain talent.Will be called upon to advice senior management on specific project issues.
